doc.ContractDescription: THIS PROPOSAL IS FOR A TWO YEAR PERIOD TO CONDUCT A CASE STUDY IN WHICH WE DEVELOP MATHEMATICAL MODELS FOR DETERMINING PREFERRED ORIENTATIONS OF GROUPS OF VOLCANIC EDIFICES IN SHIELD FIELDS ON VENUS, AND THEN APPLY THESE MODELS TO A SMALL NUMBER OF SHIELD FIELDS IN ORDER TO TEST THEIR EFFICACY AND ESTABLISH THE EXPECTED QUALITY OF THE RESULTS. THERE ARE TWO TASKS ASSOCIATED WITH THESE OBJECTIVES. TASK 1. DEVELOP MODELS TO DETERMINE SHIELD FIELD PREFERRED ORIENTATIONS. FROM TERRESTRIAL EXPERIENCE, THERE ARE TWO GENERAL CATEGORIES OF METHODS BY WHICH PREFERRED ORIENTATIONS OF POINT-LIKE FEATURES HAVE BEEN INFERRED. THESE ARE AZIMUTH METHODS AND STRIP METHODS. EACH OF THESE METHODS HAS ITS OWN STRENGTHS AND WEAKNESSES. WE PROPOSE TO ADAPT AND DEVELOP ONE MODEL OF EACH OF THESE CATEGORIES THAT ARE SUITABLE FOR VENUSIAN SHIELD FIELDS. THE END RESULT OF THIS TASK WILL BE TWO BLOCKS OF CODE THAT CAN THEN BE FURTHER TESTED WITH MAGELLAN RADAR DATA. TASK 2. VALIDATE MODELS USING SHIELD FIELDS MAPPED WITH MAGELLAN DATA. THE SECOND TASK OF THIS CASE STUDY IS TO SELECT 2-4 SHIELD FIELDS ON VENUS SUITABLE FOR INITIAL ANALYSES. A SEPARATE DIGITAL MAPPING PROJECT WILL BE CONSTRUCTED FOR EACH FIELD USING DIGITAL MAPPING TOOLS, AND THE LOCATION, ORIENTATION, AND RELATIVE STRATIGRAPHY OF ALL UNITS AND STRUCTURES IN THE REGION WILL BE DEMARCATED. CENTER POSITIONS OF EACH EDIFICE IN THE SHIELD FIELD WILL BE DETERMINED, AND THESE POSITIONS WILL BE USED AS INPUT DATA INTO THE MODELS DEVELOPED IN TASK 1. LOCAL MAPPING, SUPPLEMENTED WITH EXISTING REGIONAL MAPS, WILL BE USED TO INFER THE STRESS-STRAIN CONDITIONS PRESENT IN THE UPPER LITHOSPHERE AS CAPTURED BY THE GEOLOGIC FEATURES PRESENT. PREFERRED ORIENTATION(S) IDENTIFIED BY THE MODEL, IF FOUND, WILL BE COMPARED TO THE LOCAL STRESS-STRAIN CONDITIONS AND USED TO INFER POTENTIAL TIMING BETWEEN SHIELD FIELDS AND OTHER FEATURES AND GEOLOGIC UNITS.
